<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ901220-0147</DOCNO><DOCID>901220-0147.</DOCID><HL>   Who's News:   Allied-Signal Inc.</HL><DATE>12/20/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   ALD WNEWS</CO><IN>DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD)</IN><LP>   ALLIED-SIGNAL Inc. (Morristown, N.J.) -- David C. Hill wasnamed president of Allied Fibers, a nylon producing divisionof this advanced technology company with businesses inaerospace, automotive products and engineered materials. Mr.Hill, 44 years old, succeeds Daniel Burnham, effective Jan.1. Mr. Burnham was named president of the air research groupat the company's aerospace unit. Mr. Hill was previouslysenior vice president and general manager of Allied'sindustrial fibers unit.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>